name: Innovation Co-Lab Roots
description: The Innovation Co-Lab is a creativity incubator, focused on exploring how new and emerging technologies can fundamentally reshape the research, academic, and service missions of the university. Working with our innovation-minded colleagues around campus, we're building a model program that will elevate and inspire members of the Duke Community who are solving problems, big and small, through our ever-changing technological environment. Students, faculty, and staff of all backgrounds, interests, and skill-sets are encouraged to participate.

name: Duke Arts Create
description: Get creative in everything from clay to coding—no experience necessary! Duke Arts Create is a series of free, hands-on arts workshops designed to help Duke students, staff, and faculty develop a variety of creative skills.  Registration for the following week’s Duke Arts Create workshops goes live on Friday mornings – sign up in advance to guarantee your spot!

name: Center for Computational Thinking
description: The Center for Computational Thinking (CCT) enables computational education at Duke to ensure that every student, regardless of field of study, is prepared for the digital 21st century. Through partnerships with faculty, programs, and departments spanning a wide range of disciplines including data science, cybersecurity, policy, and ethics, we bring computational learning experiences and opportunities to the Duke community and beyond.
